reviews.review_text:
It was a nice download, thanks! On 8/10 this was available for FLAC Download, so I'm glad I got it before "they" noticed it was an Owsley SBD. Sweet!

Great sound and improvement over the other sources. Thank you Bear!

Just OMG!!! I can't believe it This is almost hard to believe it's a aud!  Bear truly was the man and the sound of this is insane beyond words...usually you can tell even a spectacular aud once the vocals start coming in but here even the vocals make you wonder "is this a matrix?"... 3 & 1/2 stars for the show and the rest is for the sound quality!  5 stars!

"We have no excuses or apologies to offer" Oregon Jam I. A big show (Eddie Money and Santana also performed), and the Dead seem to have run into their usual big show problems, with a rough start to the first set which is plagued by feedback issues. Not really feelin' it. But, hey, this is Oregon Dead. Things get going by Candyman, and although there are many, many better shows coming down the line in July, this was a fun listen. Always interesting to hear an original Bear tape as well.
